                <h2>Introduction to Mindfulness</h2>
                <p>

                    The aim of the course is to increase awareness so that we can learn how to live more fully, responding to situations with choice rather than reacting automatically.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We do this by learning to pay attention to all our experiences, including our bodily sensations, thoughts, moods and emotions, and to the small changes within them.
                </p>
                <p>

                    To focus on our experiences and the way they change, we have to become more aware of them.
                </p>
                <p>

                    The raisin exercise helps us notice what our sensations are when we fully experience something very ordinary.
                </p>
                <p>

                    The body scan helps us learn to place our attention in different parts of the body, which anchors our awareness in the present moment, and gives us more control over our attention.


                </p>
